---
import { REPO } from '../data/skills';
---
<section id="proof" class="border-y border-border/60 bg-surface/30 py-20 sm:py-28">
  <div class="container-x">
    <div class="reveal mx-auto max-w-2xl text-center">
      <p class="eyebrow">// why it works · measured</p>
      <h2 class="mt-4 font-display text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight sm:text-4xl">
        Same task. Same model. The skill is the difference.
      </h2>
      <p class="mt-4 text-muted">
        We asked Sonnet to model a bank account with a <em>unique account number</em> — a trap that
        tempts the model toward Daml contract keys, which Canton 3.x rejects. Then we compiled with
        <code class="font-mono text-accent-2">dpm build</code> on Daml SDK 3.4.11.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="reveal mx-auto mt-12 grid max-w-4xl gap-5 md:grid-cols-2">
      <!-- Without -->
      <div class="term">
        <div class="term-bar">
          <span class="term-dot bg-fail/80"></span>
          <span class="term-dot bg-border"></span>
          <span class="term-dot bg-border"></span>
          <span class="ml-2 font-mono text-xs text-muted">without-skill — dpm build</span>
        </div>
        <pre class="overflow-x-auto p-4 font-mono text-[12.5px] leading-relaxed"><code><span class="text-muted">    accountNumber : Text</span>
<span class="text-fail">    key (owner, accountNumber) : (Party, Text)</span>
<span class="text-fail">    maintainer key._1</span>
<span class="text-muted">  $ dpm build</span>
<span class="text-fail">  ✗ DsError: Contract keys.</span>
<span class="text-fail">  ✗ DAR build failed       0/3 runs</span></code></pre>
      </div>

      <!-- With -->
      <div class="term">
        <div class="term-bar">
          <span class="term-dot bg-ok/80"></span>
          <span class="term-dot bg-border"></span>
          <span class="term-dot bg-border"></span>
          <span class="ml-2 font-mono text-xs text-muted">with-skill — dpm build</span>
        </div>
        <pre class="overflow-x-auto p-4 font-mono text-[12.5px] leading-relaxed"><code><span class="text-muted">    -- keys aren't supported on Canton 3.x;</span>
<span class="text-muted">    -- uniqueness is the bank's job</span>
<span class="text-ok">    accountNumber : Text</span>
<span class="text-muted">  $ dpm build</span>
<span class="text-ok">  ✓ RESULT_BUILD_OK</span>
<span class="text-ok">  ✓ compiled              3/3 runs</span></code></pre>
      </div>
    </div>

    <p class="reveal mx-auto mt-6 max-w-2xl text-center text-xs text-muted">
      A demonstration (n=3, one task, compile-verified) — not a broad statistical claim.
      Full method, both generated files, and build logs in
      <a href={`https://github.com/${REPO}/tree/main/benchmark`} class="text-accent underline-offset-2 hover:underline" target="_blank" rel="noopener">benchmark/</a>.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>
